sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
This action creates a new user profile.

Inputs:

  • First Name - The first name of the user.
  • Last Name - The last name of the user.
  • User ID - User's user ID to sign-up. Depends on the company policy, it can be Active Directory ID, employee ID, etc that can uniquely identify the user in the company.
  • Email - User's email.
  • Phone - User's phone number.
  • Account - First Advantage assigned customer account ID.
  • Middle Name - The middle name of the user.
  • Deactivate - Specifies whether user is to be activated or deactivated, default value is false.
  • Password - Password of the user.
  • New Password - New Password of the user.
  • Root Account - First Advantage assigned root account ID.
  • Profile - First Advantage profile ID.
  • SSO Client Name - SSO client name.
  • SSO Client User - SSO client user.
  • Client IP - The IP address during registration for audit purposes.
  • Registration Date - The registration creation timestamp.
  • Roles - First Advantage user roles that will be assigned to the user.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages

  • Provided Account ID is invalid or not found.
  • User ID field appears to be empty.
  • Provided Email is invalid or not found.
  • Provided First Name is invalid or not found.
  • Provided Last Name is invalid or not found.
  • Provided Phone Number is invalid or not found.
  • SSO Client User field appears to be empty.
  • SSO Client Name field appears to be empty.
  • Provided value for either SSO Client Name or SSO Client User is invalid.
  • Provided Profile is invalid or not found.
  • Provided Registration Date is invalid.
  • Provided Roles are invalid.
  • Invalid username or password/token or the token has expired.
  • The user does not have sufficient permission to perform this action.

To use this action, the corresponding First Advantage connection and credential must be created and associated with the First Advantage Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages

  • Provided Account ID is invalid or not found.
  • User ID field appears to be empty.
  • Provided Email is invalid or not found.
  • Provided First Name is invalid or not found.
  • Provided Last Name is invalid or not found.
  • Provided Phone Number is invalid or not found.
  • SSO Client User field appears to be empty.
  • SSO Client Name field appears to be empty.
  • Provided value for either SSO Client Name or SSO Client User is invalid.
  • Provided Profile is invalid or not found.
  • Provided Registration Date is invalid.
  • Provided Roles are invalid.
  • Invalid username or password/token or the token has expired.
  • The user does not have sufficient permission to perform this action.

To use this action, the corresponding First Advantage connection and credential must be created and associated with the First Advantage Connection & Credential alias. Learn More
